metadata.definition: Functional or decorative items that are not mounted to a wall. They may be propped or supported for use or display or stacked for transport or storage.
metadata.includes: Table top framed pictures

metadata.title: Furniture and fixtures— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Furniture and fixtures that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 221 through 2262.
metadata.includes: Podiums, lecterns; water coolers; easel

metadata.title: Containers, furniture, fixtures— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Containers, furniture and fixtures where the specified container, furniture or fixture does not match codes in groups 21 through 22.

metadata.title: MACHINERY
metadata.definition: This division classifies light and heavy machinery which perform specialized functions or processes under power. Machinery is defined as a combination of smaller machines (elements or parts) which are capable of motion and are contained in a stationary or mobile frame. Heating, cooling and cleaning machinery and appliances are included in this definition. Code the whole machine as source over the specific machine that contacted the worker unless that part had separated from the whole machine. Machine parts are coded in Division 4. If an attached machine part was known to have played a significant role in the incident may be coded as secondary source if no other contributing factors (Source Division 9) have been identified.
metadata.includes: Agricultural and garden machinery; construction, logging, and mining machinery; heating, cooling, and cleaning machinery and appliances; material and personnel handling machinery (e.g., conveyors, cranes, hoists, elevators, etc.); metal, woodworking, and special material machinery;  special process machinery; flying and orbiting machinery; miscellaneous machinery
metadata.excludes: Vehicles, and machines that are primarily used for transporting people or materials (i.e. powered industrial vehicles,—material hauling and transport, tractors, forklifts) (Division 8, Vehicles). Handheld powered and nonpowered handtools are classified in major group 71 (Handtools). Hoisting accessories (45); machinery parts (46); motors, vehicle engines (462); computers, office and business machinery (Division 75)

metadata.title: Agricultural and garden machinery
metadata.definition: This major group classifies machinery used to perform specialized agricultural and garden functions or processes.
metadata.includes: Harvesting and threshing machinery; mowing machinery; plowing, planting, and fertilizing machinery; other agricultural and garden machinery
metadata.excludes: Tractors (863); construction, logging, and mining machinery (32*); grain elevators and conveyors (341); parts and materials (Division 4); animals and agricultural products (Division 5)

metadata.title: Agricultural and garden machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery used to perform specialized agricultural and garden functions or processes where a more specific code from 310 to 319 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Harvesting and threshing machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies agricultural and garden machinery which primarily perform harvesting or threshing functions.
metadata.includes: Balers; combines; agricultural harvesters and reapers; threshers

metadata.title: Harvesting and threshing machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Agricultural and garden machinery which primarily perform harvesting or threshing functions where a more specific code from 3111 to 3119 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Harvesting and threshing machinery— corn
metadata.definition: Machines or powered attachments used to perform a variety of tasks in the harvest of corn, including cutting corn, separating grain from the plant, and/or spreading remaining material over field.
metadata.includes: Corn picker; combine corn head

metadata.title: Harvesting and threshing machinery— small grain
metadata.definition: Machines or powered attachments used to perform a variety of tasks in the harvest of small grain crops, including cutting the crop, separating grain from the plant, and/or spreading remaining material over field.
metadata.includes: Cutterbar head; small grain combine; pickup head

metadata.title: Harvesting machinery— cotton
metadata.definition: Machines or powered attachments used to perform a variety of tasks in the harvest of cotton.
metadata.includes: Cotton picker; cotton stripper

metadata.title: Harvesting machinery— forage
metadata.definition: Machines or powered attachments that cut, condition and/or turn forage. The equipment may be self-propelled or pull-type.
metadata.includes: Windrower; disc cutterbar; forage harvester- hay/windrow head; forage harvester direct cut head; flail harvester; combine straw chopper; mower-conditioner; hay rake, tedder; windrow merger
metadata.excludes: Tractors (863); mowing and brush removal machinery (312)

metadata.title: Harvesting machinery— specialty crop
metadata.definition: Machines or powered attachments designed to harvest a specific type of crop.
metadata.includes: Potato harvester; sugar beet harvester; green bean harvester; pea combine; peanut combine; peanut digger; tree shakers

metadata.title: Balers, baggers
metadata.definition: Machines or powered attachments designed to gather loose materials together into bales or bags.
metadata.includes: Round hay baler; rectangular hay baler; cotton module builder; other fiber balers; silage and grain baggers
metadata.excludes: Tractors (863); bale processing and transport equipment (315)

metadata.title: Harvesting and threshing machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Agricultural and garden machinery which primarily perform harvesting or threshing functions when the specified machine does not match  codes 3111 through 3117.
metadata.includes: Forage choppers

metadata.title: Mowing and brush removal machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies agricultural and garden machinery which primarily perform grass and brush mowing functions. It excludes crop harvesting machinery
metadata.includes: Non-riding and riding lawn mowers; tractor mowers; bush hogs
metadata.excludes: Harvesting and threshing machinery (311); lawn edgers, clippers, trimmers—powered (7126); tractors (863); chippers (3234)

metadata.title: Mowing and brush removal machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Agricultural and garden machinery which primarily perform mowing functions where a more specific code from 3121 to 3129 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Agricultural rotary mower, flail mower
metadata.definition: Machine or powered attachment used to cut thick growth, bushes, and small trees.
metadata.includes: Bush hogTM; rotary mower; flail mower; shredder

metadata.title: Lawn mower— riding
metadata.definition: Mowing machinery that is ridden while either seating or standing.
metadata.includes: Standing mowers; seated mowers; lawn tractor

metadata.title: Lawn mower— walk behind
metadata.definition: Mowing machinery that is operated by pushing or self advances while the operator walks behind.
metadata.includes: Push mower

metadata.title: Mowing machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Agricultural and garden machinery which primarily perform mowing functions when the specified machine does not match  codes 3121 through 3123.
metadata.includes: Push mowers—nonpowered; roadside brush cutting attachment

metadata.title: Tillage, planting, and cultivating machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies agricultural and garden machinery which primarily perform plowing, planting, or fertilizing functions. Also included here are plows, discs, cultivators, and spreaders that are attached to tractors.
metadata.includes: Plowing and cultivating machinery; seed planting machinery; agricultural spreading machinery

metadata.title: Tillage, planting, and cultivating machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Agricultural and garden machinery which primarily perform plowing, planting, or fertilizing functions where a more specific code from 3131 to 3139 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Plowing and tilling machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery and equipment designed to break up and/or turn over soil in preparation for planting.
metadata.includes: Cultivators, harrows, discs, plows, roto tillers

metadata.title: Planting machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery designed to plant crops.
metadata.includes: Seed broadcaster; seedling planter; seedling transplanter; potato planter

metadata.title: Tillage, planting, and cultivating machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Agricultural and garden machinery which primarily perform plowing, planting, or fertilizing functions when the specified machine does not match  codes 3131 through 3132.

metadata.title: Irrigation, chemical, and fertilizer application machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery and equipment that perform tasks relating to chemical and fertilizer application, and irrigation.
metadata.excludes: Tractors (863); manure (5213); manure and sewage treatment equipment (334)

metadata.title: Irrigation, chemical, and fertilizer application machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery and equipment that perform tasks relating to chemical and fertilizer application, and irrigation where a more specific code from 3141 to 3149 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Irrigation systems
metadata.definition: Machinery and equipment that supply water to agricultural crops and landscapes. This code also includes dust suppression systems for construction and mine industrial sites.
metadata.includes: Center pivot irrigation system; traveling gun (“big gun”) irrigation system; wheel move, lateral move, or side roll irrigation system; dust suppression systems

metadata.title: Spreaders, sprayers, application equipment
metadata.definition: Equipment designed to spread or apply a variety of chemicals, fertilizers, or organic materials (e.g. manure). Includes self-propelled and pull-type equipment.
metadata.includes: Chemical sprayers; dry fertilizer spreader; solid manure spreader; manure injector; salt spreader

metadata.title: Irrigation, chemical, and fertilizer application— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery and equipment that perform tasks relating to chemical and fertilizer application, and irrigation when the specified machine does not match  codes 3141 through 3142.

metadata.title: Grain, forage, feed processing and handling machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery and equipment that perform tasks relating to the processing and handling of crops and feed outside of the growing field.

metadata.title: Grain, forage, feed processing and handling machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery and equipment that perform tasks relating to the processing and handling of crops and feed outside of the growing field where a more specific code from 3151 to 3159 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Feed grinders, crushers, mixers—agricultural
metadata.definition: Machines that process grains and forage to prepare as animal feed.
metadata.includes: Feed mixer

metadata.title: Bale and feed processing machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery and equipment that process bales and feed for storage, transport, or for preparing feed for livestock.
metadata.includes: Bale unroller

metadata.title: Bale and product transport equipment
metadata.definition: Machinery and equipment that bale loose harvested materials for transport or are designed to carry baled materials.
metadata.includes: Bale wagon; cotton module hauler; bale spear; self unloading forage box; forage dump wagon; cotton wagon

metadata.title: Grain, forage, feed processing and handling machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery and equipment that perform tasks relating to the processing and handling of crops and feed outside of the growing field when the specified machine does not match  codes 3151 through 3153.
metadata.includes: Bale spear

metadata.title: Livestock-related machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery or equipment that perform specialized tasks related to the care and processing of livestock. This may include functions such as feeding, cleaning living areas, medical care, corralling,  milking, shearing, and slaughtering.

metadata.title: Livestock-related machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery or equipment that perform specialized tasks related to the care and processing of livestock where a more specific code from 3161 to 3169 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Cattle squeeze chute
metadata.definition: Apparatus used to restrain cattle for veterinary care. May be powered or unpowered.

metadata.title: Powered cattle gates
metadata.definition: Gates that automatically push corralled cattle towards a desired entrance.

metadata.title: Powered feeding equipment
metadata.definition: Equipment designed to distribute feed to livestock.
metadata.includes: Hog feeder, poultry feeder; ground feed conveyor; self-propelled feed cart

metadata.title: Manure cleaning, scraping equipment
metadata.definition: Equipment that removes manure from barns and animal living areas by scraping it to a designated location.
metadata.includes: Slat scraper; alley scraper
metadata.excludes: Skid steer loader with scraper attachment (3222); manure and sewage agitation equipment (3343); animal manure and waste products (5213)

metadata.title: Milking parlor equipment
metadata.definition: Specialty equipment designed to milk cows or goats.
metadata.includes: Specialized milking pumps

metadata.title: Animal slaughtering equipment
metadata.definition: Specialty equipment designed to slaughter animals prior to processing.
metadata.excludes: Butchering equipment, meat processing equipment, meat grinders (361)

metadata.title: Livestock-related machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery or equipment that perform specialized tasks related to the care and processing of livestock when the specified machine does not match  codes 3161 through 3166.
metadata.includes: Straw bedding chopper; animal fiber shearing machinery (except handtools); slaughtering machinery

metadata.title: Other agricultural and garden machinery
metadata.definition: Agricultural and garden machinery which perform specific functions or processes other than those previously classified in code groups 311 through 316.
metadata.includes: snow blowers; leaf blowers
metadata.excludes: Construction, logging, and mining machinery (32); conveyors (341); elevators, lifts (343); parts and materials (Division 4); feed wagons (4741); crop-dusting aircraft (8112); tractors (863); dairy and milk processing machinery (except milking parlor machinery) (3616); vehicles, tractors, forklifts, order pickers, and other powered industrial carriers (Division 8)

metadata.title: Construction, logging, and mining machinery
metadata.definition: This major group classifies machinery which perform specific construction (or demolition), logging, and mining and extraction functions or processes.
metadata.includes: Excavating machinery; loaders; logging and wood processing machinery; mining and drilling machinery; road grading and surfacing machinery
metadata.excludes: Agricultural and garden machinery (31); material and personnel handling machinery (34); metal, woodworking, and special material machinery (35); vehicles (8); tractors (863); forklifts, order pickers, and other powered industrial carriers (862)

metadata.title: Construction, logging, and mining machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which perform specific construction (or demolition), logging, and mining and extraction functions or processes when there is not enough information to select a more detailed code from groups 321 through 329.
metadata.includes: "Construction equipment" without further description

metadata.title: Heavy earth-moving machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery which primarily perform earth moving and excavating functions.
metadata.includes: Backhoes, backhoe loaders, trackhoes, trackhoe loaders; bulldozers; front and power shovels; trenchers; draglines, dredges
metadata.excludes: Light and mini-earth moving equipment (322); drilling and extraction machinery (325); tunneling machines (3245); hooks, shackles, magnets, clamshells, grapples (442); vehicles (Division 8)

metadata.title: Heavy earth-moving machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily perform earth moving and excavating functions where a more specific code from 3211 to 3219 cannot be determined.
metadata.includes: "Digger" or "scoop" without further description

metadata.title: Excavators
metadata.definition: Excavators consist of a base cabin and a long arm with a bucket attachment at its end. It is capable of rotating 360 degrees. It can be wheeled or on tracks.
metadata.includes: Front and power shovels

metadata.title: Backhoes, trackhoes
metadata.definition: Backhoes and trackhoes are comprised of a shovel at the front and a bucket attached to a jointed arm at the rear end.
metadata.includes: Pipelayers; backhoe loaders; trackhoe loaders

metadata.title: Bucket, front-end, and pay loaders
metadata.definition: Loaders are equipped with a large front bucket to scoop, move, and load materials.
metadata.includes: Front end; pay loaders; crawl loaders; rubber tire

metadata.title: Bulldozers
metadata.definition: Bulldozers are equipped with a large metal plate in the front which can be moved up or down. Typically used in grading or removing rocks, earth.
metadata.includes: Crawler dozers; Wheeled dozers

metadata.title: Trenchers
metadata.definition: Trenchers employ a conveyor system to dig trenches. The conveyor deposits the dug material beside the trench. They are typically used to dig trenches for pipes, cables, or drainage.
metadata.includes: Trenching machines; continuous bucket excavators

metadata.title: Cable shovel, power shovel
metadata.definition: Power shovels use a bucket attached to a digging arm that is controlled by a winch and ropes or cables. They are used for digging and loading earth or fragmented rock and for mineral extraction. These are often used for very large scale projects.

metadata.title: Continuous bucket excavators
metadata.definition: A continuous digging machine employing a large wheel consisting of a continuous pattern of buckets used to scoop material as the wheel turns. They are typically used in large-scale open-pit mining operations.
metadata.includes: Bucket wheel excavator

metadata.title: Heavy earth-moving machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery or equipment whose primary function(s) are earth moving when the specified machine does not match  codes 3211 through 3217. Draglines and marine excavation machines that cast and drag a scoop through water to excavate the bottom soil are included here.
metadata.includes: Draglines; marine excavators; marine dredges; suction dredges

metadata.title: Light earth-moving machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies light equipment and machinery which primarily performs earth moving and loading operations.
metadata.excludes: Full scale and heavy earth moving machinery (321); log loaders (3236); backhoe and trackhoe loaders (3212); forklifts, order pickers, and other powered industrial carriers (862)

metadata.title: Light earth-moving machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Light earth moving equipment and machinery which primarily performs earth moving and loading operations where a more specific code from 3221 to 3229 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Mini excavators
metadata.definition: Small scale excavators, consisting of a base cabin and a long arm with a bucket attachment at its end. It is capable of rotating 360 degrees. It can be wheeled or on tracks.

metadata.title: Skid-steer loaders, mini loaders
metadata.definition: Small-sized machines which can skid on their own axis and are often used in space-constrained construction sites
metadata.includes: Skid steer loaders; mini loaders
metadata.excludes: Forklifts, order pickers, and other powered industrial carriers (862)

metadata.title: Light earth-moving machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Light equipment and machinery which primarily performs earth moving and loading operations when the specified machine does not match  codes 3221 through 3222.
metadata.excludes: Forklifts, order pickers, and other powered industrial carriers (862)

metadata.title: Logging and wood processing machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery which primarily performs specialized logging and wood processing operations.
metadata.includes: Chippers; logging skidders; debarkers; harvesters (logging); log loaders
metadata.excludes: Agricultural harvesters (311); other loaders (321); material and personnel handling machinery (34); metal, woodworking, and special material machinery (35); paper production machinery (364); other grapples (44)

metadata.title: Logging and wood processing machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily performs specialized logging and wood processing operations where a more specific code from 3231 to 3239 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Mechanical harvesters— logging
metadata.definition: Machines that cut trees and may also perform a combination of other tasks including bunching trees into bundles, cutting logs on site, or other processing activities.
metadata.includes: Fellers, feller-bunchers, feller-forwarders, log forwarders, log harvesters

metadata.title: Forwarding and yarding machinery— except feller-forwarders
metadata.definition: Machines designed to move trees from site of harvest to landing area. Yarders use a cable and tower to pull suspended or partially suspended trees over the harvest area.
metadata.includes: Yarder, tower yarder; forwarder

metadata.title: Skidders— cable and grapple
metadata.definition: Machines that grab logs or whole trees with grapples or choker cables. They typically lift the front ends of logs off the ground to pull them to a desired location.
metadata.includes: Logging skidders
metadata.excludes: Earth moving machinery (321); Skid steer loader (3222)

metadata.title: Chippers
metadata.definition: Machines used for reducing tree limbs or trunks into smaller woodchips. They are often portable and can be towed behind a vehicle.
metadata.includes: Mulchers, masticators

metadata.title: Log processing machinery
metadata.definition: Machines typically used at log landing site to delimb and cut trees into logs.
metadata.includes: Delimbers, debarkers, slashers

metadata.title: Log loaders
metadata.definition: Machines designed to load and unload logs onto trucks for transport.
metadata.includes: Heel boom and wheeled log loaders; LeTourneau log loader; loader crane

metadata.title: Logging and wood processing machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily performs specialized logging and wood processing operations when the specified machine does not match  codes 3231 through 3236.
metadata.includes: Firewood processors; log splitters; combination log processing machinery

metadata.title: Mining and tunneling machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery which perform specialized mining and tunneling operations including accessing subterranean locations via tunneling, removal of valuable earth mineral from underground and some selected processing tasks. Many mining-type machines are used for excavating in the construction industry and should be classified accordingly.
metadata.includes: Mineral sorters, separators, concentrators; tunneling machines; oil drilling rigs and machinery
metadata.excludes: Offshore oil platforms (631); pump jacks (3252); Drilling machines, drilling augers (325)

metadata.title: Mining and tunneling machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which perform specialized mining and tunneling operations where a more specific code from 3241 to 3249 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Longwall shearer
metadata.definition: Machines designed to shear off the face of a coal seem in longwall mining operations.

metadata.title: Powered supports
metadata.definition: Movable powered wall shoring systems, typically operated via hydraulic cylinders.
metadata.includes: Hydraulic roof supports; powered wall supports

metadata.title: Compactors, crushers, pulverizers—earth, mineral
metadata.definition: Machinery designed to reduce the size of mined materials by compacting, crushing or other means of breaking apart.
metadata.includes: Coal breakers; coal crushers

metadata.title: Mineral sorters, separators, concentrators
metadata.definition: Machinery that separates valuable minerals from the other raw materials. Equipment may separate using various methods including optical sorting, gravity separation, magnetic or electrostatic separation, or flotation separation.
metadata.includes: Optical sorting; gravity separation; magnetic or electrostatic separation; or flotation separation; mineral agitators

metadata.title: Tunneling machines
metadata.definition: Machinery that is generally used to bore horizontal holes.
metadata.includes: Bore tunneling machines; horizontal boring machines; directional drilling machines; micro-tunneling machines; mole machine; continuous miners

metadata.title: Mining and tunneling machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery which perform specialized mining and tunneling operations when the specified machine does not match  codes 3241 through 3245.
metadata.includes: Mineral property analyzers

metadata.title: Drilling and extraction machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery and equipment used to drill wells and extract resources such as oil, gas or water. Due to the customized nature of individual oil wells, systems of equipment have been grouped by function within this code block. Some parts and equipment that commonly appear in drilling and extraction apparatus may be classified in other groups or Divisions.
metadata.excludes: Incident involving the entire oil rig (Division 6); augers used as conveyors (3416); portable handheld augers and drills (71)

metadata.title: Drilling and extraction machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery and equipment used to drill wells and extract resources such as oil, gas or water where a more specific code from 3251 to 3259 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Drilling machines, drill apparatus
metadata.definition: Smaller mobile drilling machine used to drill holes for smaller extraction, sampling, and well digging projects
metadata.includes: Continuous miners; mechanical miners; diamond drills; rock drills; jet flame drills; water-jet drills; well drill bits; drill augers; truck mounted drilling machines

metadata.title: Oil well pump
metadata.definition: The over ground drive for a reciprocating piston pump in an oil well. It is used to mechanically lift liquid out of the well if not enough bottom hole pressure exists for the liquid to flow all the way to the surface. The arrangement is commonly used for onshore wells producing little oil.
metadata.includes: Sucker rod pump; pump jack; oil derrick pump

metadata.title: Rotary system equipment
metadata.definition: The rotary system includes all of the equipment used to achieve bit rotation.
metadata.includes: Rotary table, kelly, kelly bushings, master bushings, kelly spinner, swivel

metadata.title: Wellhead valves
metadata.definition: The assembly of valves, spools, and fittings used to regulate the flow of pipes and prevent blowouts in an oil well, gas well, water injection well, water disposal well, gas injection well, condensate well and other types of wells.
metadata.includes: Christmas tree; blow-out preventer (BOP) stack

metadata.title: Drilling fluids systems
metadata.definition: The assembly of equipment used to store, circulate and clean drilling fluids.
metadata.includes: Fluid circulation system; mud; mud pit; mud tank; shale shaker; mud cleaner; mud agitators; heater treater

metadata.title: Rig tongs, power tongs
metadata.definition: Large self-locking wrenches that are used to spin pipe and apply torque.
metadata.includes: Chisel tongs; casing tongs; power tongs; rotary tongs and manual tongs

metadata.title: Heater treater
metadata.definition: A pressure vessel that uses heat and residence time to separate clean, dry oil from incoming fluids. It is part of the oil dehydration process.

metadata.title: Drilling and extraction machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery and equipment used to drill wells and extract resources such as oil, gas or water when the specified machine does not match  codes 3251 through 3257.
metadata.includes: walking systems, stompers
metadata.excludes: Offshore oil platforms (631); derricks, draw works (3427)

metadata.title: Road grading and surfacing machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery which primarily perform road grading and surfacing operations.
metadata.includes: Asphalt and concrete spreaders; asphalt and concrete paving machines, pavers; rollers compactors—construction; graders, scrapers—construction; milling machines, cold planers, and road profilers; road recyclers, road reclaimers; material transfer machines; line marking and striping machinery
metadata.excludes: Construction, logging, and mining machinery (32*); street sweeping and cleaning machinery (893); vehicles (8*)

metadata.title: Road grading and surfacing machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily perform road grading and surfacing operations where a more specific code from 3261 to 3269 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Asphalt and concrete spreaders
metadata.definition: Equipment to fill and spread concrete and asphalt.
metadata.includes: Screeds

metadata.title: Concrete paving machines, pavers
metadata.definition: Machinery that extrudes a paved concrete surface with or without the use of forms or molds.  They can be used to pave flat surfaces, curbs and gutters, roadway median barriers, bridge parapets, etc.
metadata.includes: Slipform pavers; curb-and-gutter pavers

metadata.title: Rollers, compactors—construction
metadata.definition: Equipment used to compact and smooth road base materials or paving materials (e.g. asphalt).
metadata.includes: Oil compactors; asphalt rollers and compactors; landfill compactors; vibratory rollers and compactors; pneumatic rollers and compactors; steam rollers

metadata.title: Graders, scrapers—construction
metadata.definition: Equipment used to level and smooth road and ground surfaces.
metadata.includes: Elevating scrapers; coal bowl scrapers; open bowl scrapers; push-pull scrapers

metadata.title: Milling machines, cold planers, and road profilers
metadata.definition: Road profilers and milling machines perform a range of road paving activities, including excavate the road base, crushing the old road material and filling the partnering truck at the same time for either recycling or disposal.
metadata.includes: Road recyclers; road reclaimers

metadata.title: Material transfer machines— construction
metadata.definition: Material transfer machines transfer hot paving asphalt from the truck to the paving machine while blending the old and new material together to allow for continuous paving.
metadata.includes: Transfer machines; shuttle buggies; windrow machines

metadata.title: Road grading and surfacing machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily perform road grading and surfacing operations when the specified machine does not match  codes 3261 through 3266.
metadata.includes: Road line marking and striping machinery

metadata.title: Other construction, logging, and mining machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies construction, logging, and mining machinery which perform specific functions or processes other than those previously classified.
metadata.includes: Cement mixers (except truck mounted); compactors, tamping machinery; pile extractors
metadata.excludes: Agricultural and garden machinery (31); material and personnel handling machinery (34); metal, woodworking, and special material machinery (35); vehicles (8); tractors (863); truck-mounted cement mixers (3443)

metadata.title: Agitators, mixers—earth, mineral
metadata.definition: Machines used to mix or continuously move materials to maintain uniform consistency.
metadata.includes: Cement mixers (except trucks)
metadata.excludes: Truck-mounted cement mixers (8424); mineral agitators, sorters (3244)

metadata.title: Pile drivers, tamping machinery
metadata.definition: Machines used to drive piles or other materials into the ground, typically by means of striking force.
metadata.includes: Drop hammers; pile hammers; air, diesel, and vibratory hammers; combination pile driving and extracting units; pile hammer machinery

metadata.title: Other construction, logging, and mining machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery used in construction, logging or mining when the specified machine does not match descriptions of codes 320 through 329.
metadata.includes: Pile extractors; segmental bridge launching machine

metadata.title: Heating, cooling, cleaning, and waste handling machinery
metadata.definition: This major group classifies machinery which perform specific heating, cooling, and cleaning functions or processes.
metadata.includes: Cooling and humidifying machinery and appliances; heating and cooking machinery and appliances; washers, dryers, and cleaning machinery and appliances
metadata.excludes: Boilers (2121); dairy and milk processing machinery (3616); industrial furnaces and forging machinery (3513); distilling and rectifying machinery (3672); incinerators (3344); vending machines (391); vehicle fans (4624); welding & cutting machinery (359); powered welding and heating handtools (718)

metadata.title: Heating, cooling, cleaning, and waste handling machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which performs specific heating, cooling, and cleaning functions or processes where a more specific code from 3310 to 339 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Cooling and humidifying machinery, appliances
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery which primarily performs cooling and humidifying functions.
metadata.includes: Air conditioners; fans, blowers; humidifiers, dehumidifiers, vaporizers; refrigerators, freezers, ice makers
metadata.excludes: Dairy and milk processing machinery (3616); vehicle fans (4624)

metadata.title: Cooling and humidifying machinery, appliances— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily performs cooling and humidifying functions where a more specific code from 3311 to 3319 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Air conditioning units
metadata.definition: Machinery that cools and dehumidifies interior air.

metadata.title: Fans, blowers—wall, floor, ceiling, ventilation
metadata.definition: Machinery that moves air around an area.
metadata.includes: House fans; Industrial fans

metadata.title: Humidifiers, dehumidifiers, vaporizers
metadata.definition: Machinery that amends interior air humidity.
metadata.includes: Humidor

metadata.title: Refrigerators, freezers, ice makers
metadata.definition: A compartment or cabinet that preserves and maintains items at very cool temperatures.
metadata.includes: walk in freezer

metadata.title: Cooling and humidifying machinery, appliances— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily performs cooling and humidifying functions when the specified machine does not match  codes 3311 through 3314.

metadata.title: Heating and cooking machinery, appliances
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery which primarily performs general heating and cooking functions, as well as fabric pressing and steaming functions.
metadata.includes: Beverage heating and percolating equipment and appliances; broiling and frying equipment and appliances; fabric pressers and ironing appliances; furnaces, heaters; kilns; ranges, cooking ovens, grills, toasters, food warmers; steaming equipment and appliances
metadata.excludes: Boilers (2121); dairy and milk processing machinery (3616); industrial furnaces and forging machinery (351); distilling and rectifying machinery (3672); incinerators (3344); vending machines (391); powered welding and heating handtools (718)

metadata.title: Heating and cooking machinery, appliances— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily performs general heating and cooking functions, as well as fabric pressing and steaming functions where a more specific code from 3321 to 3329 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Beverage heating and percolating equipment, appliances
metadata.definition: Machines and appliances that involve heating water or other liquids to make beverages.
metadata.includes: Coffee makers; hot water makers; espresso machines

metadata.title: Frying and pressurized cooking equipment, appliances
metadata.definition: Machines and appliances that rely on hot oil or high temperatures under pressure to cook food.
metadata.includes: Pressure fryers; deep fryers; pressure-cookers

metadata.title: Fabric pressers and ironing appliances
metadata.definition: Machinery used to press fabric using dry or steam heat.
metadata.includes: Handheld irons and steamers; industrial irons and fabric presses

metadata.title: Steaming equipment and appliances—except fabric presses
metadata.definition: Appliances and equipment that use steam to perform a task.
metadata.includes: Steam cleaners, sterilizers; steam cookers; wallpaper steamers

metadata.title: Furnaces, heaters
metadata.definition: Appliances fired by gas, oil, or wood in which air or water is heated for building climate control or other purposes.
metadata.includes: Domestic furnaces; potbellied stoves; Franklin stoves; gas and oil furnaces; solar heaters; heating units; space heaters; hot-water heaters; radiators; registers; furnace

metadata.title: Cooking and food-warming machinery— except pressurized
metadata.definition: Appliances used indoors and outdoors for cooking food with dry heat. These may be heated by electricity, gas or wood.
metadata.includes: Kitchen ranges; cook tops; grills—outdoor, indoor; roasters; hibachis; kitchen stoves; microwave ovens; toasters ovens; waffle irons; wood fired oven (i.e. for pizza); smokers; Camping stoves, portable stoves;

metadata.title: Kilns
metadata.definition: Furnaces or ovens for curing, baking, or drying.
metadata.includes: Glass furnace; pottery kiln; brick kiln

metadata.title: Heating and cooking machinery, appliances— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily performs general heating and cooking functions, as well as fabric pressing and steaming functions when the specified machine does not match  codes 3321 through 3327.

metadata.title: Cleaning machinery, appliances
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery which primarily performs washing, drying, and cleaning functions in either residential or industrial settings.
metadata.includes: Car washing machinery, except for hand-held power washers; clothes dryers; clothes washers; dishwashers; hair and hand dryers; vacuum cleaners; other filtering and purifying machinery
metadata.excludes: Kilns (3327); paper production dryers (364); paper production washers, bleachers, refiners (364); street sweeping and cleaning machinery (893); Power washers, pressure washers (3543)

metadata.title: Cleaning machinery, appliances— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily performs washing, drying, and cleaning functions for specific products where a more specific code from 3331 to 3339 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Car or vehicle washing machinery
metadata.definition: Machines for washing the exterior of vehicles.
metadata.includes: Commercial car washes

metadata.title: Clothes washers, dryers
metadata.definition: Machines and appliances for washing and drying clothing and textiles.
metadata.includes: Industrial and residential clothes washers and dryers; laundromat washers and dryers

metadata.title: Dishwashers
metadata.definition: Machines and appliances for washing dishes.
metadata.includes: Industrial and residential dishwashers

metadata.title: Floor and upholstery cleaners— except vacuums
metadata.definition: Machines and appliances for cleaning upholstery, rugs, and floors, whether carpeted and hard finish.
metadata.includes: Rug shampooer, floor scrubbers, polishers, waxers, truck mounted or other

metadata.title: Industrial vacuums
metadata.definition: Machines and appliances that use suction to clean or perform other tasks in an industrial environment. These include wet and dry vacuums.
metadata.includes: Shop vacTM; truck mounted vacuum

metadata.title: Cleaning machinery, appliances— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily performs washing, drying, and cleaning functions for specific products when the specific machine is known but does not match descriptions of codes 3331 through 3335.
metadata.includes: Zamboni
metadata.excludes: Cleaning handtools (717); hair dryers, hand dryers (7184)

metadata.title: Waste management machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery that handles and processes waste materials, including solid waste, recyclables, and sewage and waste water.

metadata.title: Waste management machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery that handles and processes waste materials where a more specific code from 3341 to 3349 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Trash compactors, shredders
metadata.definition: Machines that crush and compact waste materials to achieve a smaller volume.
metadata.includes: Scrap metal compactors; trash balers; hard drive crushers, shredders

metadata.title: Garbage disposals
metadata.definition: Devices that are installed under sinks between the drain and the trap that shred food waste into pieces small enough to pass through plumbing.

metadata.title: Manure and sewage agitation equipment
metadata.definition: Equipment designed to agitate and aerate human or animal waste to speed decomposition.
metadata.includes: Agitator boat; pit agitator

metadata.title: Incinerators
metadata.definition: Apparatus for burning remains or waste material at high temperatures until it is reduced to ash.
metadata.includes: Cremation ovens; industrial waste incinerators

metadata.title: Waste management machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery that handles and processes waste materials when the specific machine is known but not specified in codes 3341 through 3344.
metadata.includes: Garbage sorting machinery; screening machines; air separating machines

metadata.title: Heating, cooling, cleaning, and waste handling machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: This source group classifies heating, cooling, and cleaning machinery and appliances which perform functions other than those previously classified in codes within groups 331 through 334.

metadata.title: Material and personnel handling machinery
metadata.definition: This major group classifies machinery which perform specialized material and personnel handling functions or processes, including lifting and lowering and conveying from one location to another.
metadata.includes: Gravity conveyors; powered conveyors; cranes; overhead hoists; derricks; elevators; jacks; winders, unwinders
metadata.excludes: Agricultural and garden machinery (31); construction, logging, and mining machinery (32); logging and wood processing machinery (323); hoisting accessories (45); machine, tool, and electric parts (46); scaffolds, staging (634); vehicles (8); forklifts (8621)

metadata.title: Material and personnel handling machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which perform specialized material and personnel handling functions or processes when a more specific code from groups 341 to 349 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Conveyors
metadata.definition: This source group classifies powered and nonpowered conveyors that raise or lower materials or advance them along a level path.
metadata.includes: Belt conveyors; belt loaders; bucket, cup conveyors; chain conveyors; live roller conveyors; pan conveyors; pneumatic conveyors; screw and auger conveyors, such as grain augers; slot conveyors

metadata.title: Conveyors— unspecified
metadata.definition: Powered and nonpowered conveyors where a more specific code from 3411 to 3419 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Chutes
metadata.definition: A sloping channel or slide for conveying materials to a lower level via gravity.
metadata.includes: Construction chute; trash chute; spiral chutes

metadata.title: Conveyors—belt, slot, chain
metadata.definition: An apparatus using a continuous moving circle of fabric or rubber (band conveyor), slotted metal (slot conveyor) or chain (chain conveyor) to convey objects from one place to another.
metadata.includes: Live roller conveyors (belt or chain driven); telescoping conveyor, extendable conveyor

metadata.title: Conveyors—bucket, cup, pan
metadata.definition: An apparatus for conveying flowable bulk materials upward by means of a continuous circle of buckets, cups, or pans.
metadata.includes: Grain elevator

metadata.title: Conveyors—roller, wheel
metadata.definition: An apparatus consisting of a series of rollers supported in a frame over which objects are advanced, manually, by gravity or by power.
metadata.includes: Gravity conveyor; skatewheel conveyor; ball transfer

metadata.title: Conveyors—pneumatic, tube
metadata.definition: Pneumatic conveyors move materials in an enclosed tube system by means of compressed air or by means of a vacuum.
metadata.includes: Vacuum conveyors

metadata.title: Conveyors—screw, auger
metadata.definition: A screw conveyor or auger conveyor is an apparatus that uses a rotating helical screw blade, often within a tube, to move liquid or granular materials.
metadata.includes: Grain auger

metadata.title: Conveyors— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Powered and nonpowered conveyors when the specific machine is known but not specified in codes 3411 through 3416.
metadata.includes: Dry-cleaning and garment conveyors; telescoping conveyor, 'extendo'

metadata.title: Cranes
metadata.definition: This source group classifies cranes which primarily are used for lifting heavy weights by means of a movable projecting arm or a horizontal beam traveling on an overhead support.
metadata.includes: Floating cranes; gantry cranes; hammerhead cranes; mobile, truck, or rail-mounted cranes; monorail and underhung cranes; overhead cranes; portal, tower, and pillar cranes; derricks and related equipment

metadata.title: Cranes— unspecified
metadata.definition: Cranes where a more specific code from 3421 to 3429 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Cranes—truck-mounted
metadata.definition: Cranes that are mounted to a truck for ease of transport.
metadata.includes: Boom truck; telescopic boom truck cranes; articulating, knuckle boom truck cranes

metadata.title: Cranes—rail-mounted
metadata.definition: Cranes that move along railway train tracks that are shared with locomotives.
metadata.includes: Railroad cranes

metadata.title: Cranes—floating, barge mounted
metadata.definition: Cranes erected on barges or floating platforms.

metadata.title: Cranes—other mobile cranes
metadata.definition: Other types of cranes designed to be easily transported between locations
metadata.includes: Crawler cranes, all-terrain cranes, rough-terrain cranes

metadata.title: Cranes—tower, self-erecting, pillar, hammerhead
metadata.definition: Cranes that are designed to be permanent or semi-permanent.
metadata.includes: Dock cranes (except rail mounted)

metadata.title: Cranes—gantry, overhead, monorail, container
metadata.definition: Cranes built atop a gantry, which is a structure used to straddle an object or workspace. These may large scale of "full" cranes or smaller shop cranes. The gantry itself may be rail-mounted or stationary.
metadata.includes: Ship lift; portal cranes; shop crane

metadata.title: Derricks and related equipment
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily function as derricks, hoisting mechanisms which use ropes or cables running on pulleys.
metadata.includes: A-frame derricks; basket derricks; breast derricks; gin pole derricks; guy derricks; oil drilling derricks

metadata.title: Cranes— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Cranes that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3421 through 3427.
metadata.includes: Other fixed or stationary cranes; jib cranes, bulk loading cranes

metadata.title: Elevators, hoists, lifts
metadata.definition: This source group includes machinery, such as elevators and aerial lifts, used to raise and lift workers to a height needed to perform work tasks. It also classifies material handling machinery which is primarily used to lift and lower a load along a fixed vertical path of travel with intermittent motion.
metadata.includes: Building elevators; aerial lifts, scissor lifts;  dumbwaiters; boom trucks; truck mounted and non-truck mounted bucket or basket hoists, aerial lifts, cherry pickers
metadata.excludes: Conveyors (341); cranes (342) scaffolds, staging (634); forklifts (8621); portable car jacks, scissor jacks (344); elevator shafts (6145);  unattached lift and elevator parts (i.e. electric motors, cables, pulleys, and counterweights) (Division 4); Truck-mounted bucket or basket hoists, aerial lifts, cherry pickers (when involved in incidents that are classified as Transportation) (8425)

metadata.title: Elevators, hoists, lifts— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery used to raise and lift workers to a height needed to perform work tasks where a more specific code from 3431 to 3439 cannot be determined.
metadata.includes: Truck mounted lifts

metadata.title: Elevators
metadata.definition: A platform or compartment housed in a shaft for raising and lowering people or things to different floors or levels.
metadata.includes: Building elevators; mine elevators; electric elevators; hydraulic elevators; hand-operated elevators
metadata.excludes: Construction elevators (343); dumbwaiters (3432); elevator shafts (6145); hoisting accessories such as fixtures, hooks, or slings (45)

metadata.title: Dumbwaiters
metadata.definition: Small elevators for carrying smaller items between the floors of a building.

metadata.title: Vehicle Hoists, lifts
metadata.definition: Machine by which automobiles are hoisted above the floor to give access to the underparts.
metadata.includes: Car lift; boat lift (except gantry cranes)
metadata.excludes: Truck mounted lifts (8425); tow trucks (8421); jacks (344)

metadata.title: Hoists, lifts— overhead, cable
metadata.definition: Electric, manual, and pneumatic hoists for raising and lowering material with using a cable and pulley system while either freely suspended or attached to a boom or tower.
metadata.includes: Aircraft loading hoists; powered and manual overhead hoists; construction hoists, construction elevators, buck hoists
metadata.excludes: Elevators (3431); hoisting accessories such as fixtures, hooks, or slings (45); patient hoist (745); automotive lifts (3433)

metadata.title: Hoists, lifts— scissor, telescoping
metadata.definition: Machinery used to raise materials and persons via a platform that is mounted on folding or telescoping arms is used to provide access to elevated work areas or to help raise or lower unit loads. They may or may not  be truck mounted.
metadata.includes: Manlifts; aerial work platform, aerial lift; scissor lift; strait arm; telescoping arm lift; cherry pickers (except truck mounted)

metadata.title: Elevators, hoists, lifts— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Lifting and hoisting machinery that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3431 through 3435.
metadata.includes: Rack & pinion hoists
metadata.excludes: Hoisting accessories such as fixtures, hooks, or slings (45)

metadata.title: Jacks
metadata.definition: Machines and equipment which are primarily used to lift, bolster, hoist, or move something heavy a short distance.
metadata.includes: Hydraulic, mechanical, or pneumatic jacks; bottle jacks; scissor jacks; portable car jacks; trailer landing gear
metadata.excludes: Elevators (3431); oil well pump jacks (3252); pallet jacks, motorized (8623); pallet jacks, non-motorized (2132); automobile hoists, lifts (3433); scissor lifts (3435)

metadata.title: Pumps— except oil well
metadata.definition: Machines that use suction or pressure to raise or move liquids, or force air into vessels.
metadata.includes: Centrifugal pumps, gasoline pumps; concrete pumps; fluid power pumps; water, sump pumps; bike tire pump

metadata.title: Air compressors
metadata.definition: A machine that creates and  dispenses pressurized air (i.e., compressed air) to be used in a variety of applications, such as tire inflation, cleaning, or filling of pressure containers.
metadata.includes: attached air hoses

metadata.title: Material handling and warehousing machinery
metadata.definition: This source group includes machinery and equipment used to handle large volumes of materials in preparation for storage and transport.
metadata.includes: Inventory machinery; packing and bundling; stacking; binning; order picking
metadata.excludes: Forklifts (8621); powered industrial carriers (8622); airport utility vehicles (8624); powered pallet jacks 8623)

metadata.title: Material handling and warehousing machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery and equipment used to handle large volumes of materials in preparation for storage and transport where a more specific code from 3471 to 3479 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Order picking and packing machinery
metadata.definition: Specialized equipment designed to pick orders and/or package them. These may be autonomous or robotic.
metadata.includes: Autonomous order picking equipment

metadata.title: Stacking machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery used to stack bundles of materials for storage and transport.
metadata.includes: Autonomous or robotic stacking machinery

metadata.title: Material handling and warehousing machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Material handling and warehousing machinery that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3471 through 3472.
metadata.includes: Winders, unwinders; baling and strapping machinery; inventory scanning equipment (non-autonomous)

metadata.title: Other material and personnel handling machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Material and personnel handling machinery that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3410 through 3479.
metadata.excludes: Agricultural and garden machinery (31); construction, logging, and mining machinery (32); logging and wood processing machinery (323); hoisting accessories (45); machine, tool, and electric parts (46); vehicles (8); forklifts (8621); packaging, bottling, wrapping, and bundling machinery (363); agricultural balers (3117)

metadata.title: Metal, woodworking, and special material machinery
metadata.definition: This major group classifies machinery which primarily perform specific material cutting, shaping, or forming functions or processes. Special material machinery includes those that process plastic, rubber, concrete and other special materials. Many machines classified here are referred to as "Machine Tools"—machines that make the parts for other machines. These machines are commonly used in the manufacturing industries, but may be utilized in other industries as well.
metadata.includes: Bending, rolling, shaping machinery; boring, drilling, planing, milling machinery; extruding, injecting, forming, molding machinery; grinding, polishing machinery; lathes; presses (except printing); sawing machinery; threading and tapping machines; electrochemical and discharge machinery (EDM); laser cutting, pressure fluid cutting; welding machinery
metadata.excludes: Agricultural and garden machinery (31); construction, logging, and mining machinery (32); drilling and extraction machinery (325); material and personnel handling machinery (34); food slicers, meat grinders (361); paper production machinery (364); textile, apparel, leather production machinery (366); handtools (71)

metadata.title: Metal, woodworking, and special material machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily perform specific material cutting, shaping, or forming functions or processes where a more specific code from groups 351 to 359 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Extruding, injecting, forming, molding machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery which primarily casts, extrudes, forges, or injects molten metal, plastics, rubber, or other special materials to produce work pieces.
metadata.includes: Casting machinery; extruding machinery; forging machinery; plastic injection molding machinery
metadata.excludes: Heaters, home furnaces, cooking ovens, industrial ovens used for drying agricultural products, kilns (332); dies, molds, patterns (4643)

metadata.title: Extruding, injecting, forming, molding machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Extruding, injecting, forming, molding machinery where a more specific code from 3511 to 3519 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Casting machinery
metadata.definition: Casting machines shape and form molten metal and other material into various objects and parts by the use of a mold or die.
metadata.includes: Ingot molding machinery, Molding machinery (except plastic)

metadata.title: Extruding machinery
metadata.definition: Extrusion machines mold and shape unformed material in a continuous profile to produce lengths of stock forms. They are used mainly in the plastics, metals, and composite-forming industries.
metadata.includes: Plastic extruders, rubber extruders, wire extruders

metadata.title: Forging machinery
metadata.definition: Forging machines use compressive force and a high workpiece temperature to shape metal.
metadata.includes: Blast furnaces; industrial furnaces; cold forging machinery; industrial forging ovens; forges; smelters; hot forging machinery, Basic Oxygen Furnace (BOF)
metadata.excludes: Incinerators (3344);  industrial ovens used for drying agricultural products, kilns (332)

metadata.title: Plastic injection molding machinery
metadata.definition: Machines that melt plastic and then inject it into a mold, where it cools and solidifies into the desired form.
metadata.includes: Plastic molding machinery

metadata.title: 3D printing machinery
metadata.definition: 3D printing or additive manufacturing machinery that  produces three dimensional solid objects from a digital file by laying down successive layers of material until the object is created.
metadata.includes: Stereolithography (SLA); digital light processing (DLP); fused deposition modeling (FDM); selective laser sintering (SLS); selective laser melting (SLM); electronic beam melting (EBM); laminated object manufacturing (LOM); binder jetting (BJ)

metadata.title: Extruding, injecting, forming, molding machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Extruding, injecting, forming, molding machinery that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3511 through 3515.

metadata.title: Bending, rolling, shaping, stamping machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery which primarily perform bending, rolling, shaping, or stamping functions on metal or other materials.
metadata.includes: Bending, crimping machines; shearing machines; rolling mills, rolling, calendering machinery
metadata.excludes: Paper production machinery, food production machinery, textile production machinery (36)

metadata.title: Bending, rolling, shaping, stamping machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily perform bending, rolling, or shaping functions on metal or other materials where a more specific code from 3521 to 3529 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Stamping machinery, presses— except printing
metadata.definition: Machines that exert pressure over to form, shape, cut or assemble metal or other materials.
metadata.includes: Mechanical, hydraulic and forging presses; assembly press; brake press; punch press

metadata.title: Bending, crimping machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery that shapes materials by applying pressure to bend or crimp.

metadata.title: Shearing machinery
metadata.definition: Machines with blades or rotary disks for cutting sheets, plates, or bars of materials (i.e. metal).

metadata.title: Rolling mills, rolling, calendering machinery
metadata.definition: Machines that use rollers or plates to smooth and glaze cloth, rubber, or paper, or to form these materials into thin sheets.
metadata.includes: Calenders

metadata.title: Winders, unwinders
metadata.definition: Machines for wrapping materials around a spindle, spool or bobbin.
metadata.includes: Wire coils; rope winding

metadata.title: Bending, rolling, shaping, stamping machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Bending, rolling, and shaping machinery that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3521 through 3525.

metadata.title: Boring, planing, milling machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery which primarily perform material cutting functions (boring, drilling, planing, and milling).
metadata.includes: Stationary drills; planing machines; milling machines; reaming machines
metadata.excludes: Construction, logging, and mining machinery (32); drilling and extraction machinery (325); paper production machinery (364); handtools (71); boring and drilling handtools (711)

metadata.title: Boring, planing, milling machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Boring, drilling, planing or milling machinery where a more specific code from 3531 to 3539 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Stationary drills, milling machinery
metadata.definition: Drills create holes in a workpiece using a rotating cutting "bit". Milling machines perform a variety of functions including machining flat surfaces or irregular surfaces.  Both of these functions may be combined into a single machine, or machine center,  which do a number of different operations, including milling, drilling, boring, facing, spotting, counterboring, threading, and tapping—in a single setup.
metadata.includes: Drill presses, Jig boring machines, Drilling machines, Radial drills, Gang drills;  Broaching machines, Machining centers

metadata.title: Planing mills
metadata.definition: Planers cut large, flat surfaces on a workpiece, or cut many small parts simultaneously.

metadata.title: Boring, reaming, routing, notching machinery
metadata.definition: Machines used to bore or enlarge holes, flutes or notches in materials. The boring process enlarges and trues existing holes. Reamers are used to produce precise hole sizes with a smooth finish.

metadata.title: Lathes
metadata.definition: A lathe is a machine tool that rotates a workpiece about an axis to perform various operations such as cutting, sanding, knurling, drilling, deformation, facing, and turning to create an object with symmetry about that axis.
metadata.includes: Metalworking lathes; woodworking lathes

metadata.title: Threading, tapping machinery
metadata.definition: Threading machinery creates external threads (i.e. on shafts/rods). Tapping machinery creates internal threads (i.e. for the inside of a nut). These are used to make connections for pipes and fittings.
metadata.includes: Bolt and pipe threading

metadata.title: Boring, planing, milling machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Boring, drilling, planing or milling machinery that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3531 through 3535.
metadata.includes: Gear-cutting machinery; nibbling machines

metadata.title: Industrial surfacing and finishing machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery which primarily perform material surfacing and finishing operations (by grinding or polishing).
metadata.includes: Grinders, abraders; honing, polishing, lapping machinery
metadata.excludes: Meat grinders (3613); powered surfacing handtools, buffers, polishers, waxers—powered, powered hand grinders (716)

metadata.title: Industrial surfacing and finishing machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Industrial material surfacing and finishing machinery where a more specific code from 3541 to 3549 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Grinders, abraders
metadata.definition: Grinding machines usually employ a coarse, abrasive wheel to smooth and remove imperfections.
metadata.includes: Centerless grinders, internal grinders, cylindrical grinders, surface grinders

metadata.title: Honing, polishing, lapping machinery
metadata.definition: Honing and lapping machines use abrasive sticks, plates, or rolls for precise metal-finishing operations.

metadata.title: Pressure washers
metadata.definition: Pressure washers typically use cold or normal water while power washers use a high pressurized stream of hot water to remove loose paint, mold, etc. from surfaces and objects such as buildings, vehicles and concrete surfaces.
metadata.includes: Power washer; pressure washers

metadata.title: Sandblasting machinery
metadata.definition: Sandblasting or abrasive blasting machinery is designed to propel a stream of abrasive material against a surface under high pressure to smooth a rough surface, roughen a smooth surface, shape a surface or remove surface contaminants.

metadata.title: Sanding machinery
metadata.definition: Industrial equipment used to sand surfaces.
metadata.includes: Floor sander; industrial sander; belt sander (except handheld); drum sander

metadata.title: Painting, priming, metal coating machinery
metadata.definition: Industrial equipment used to apply paint, primer and powder finishes to surfaces.
metadata.includes: Powder coating guns; powder coating booth
metadata.excludes: Portable paint sprayers, paint brushes and rollers (Division 7); powder coat curing ovens (332)

metadata.title: Industrial surfacing and finishing machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Industrial material surfacing and finishing machinery that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3541 through 3546.
metadata.includes: Paint mixing machinery

metadata.title: Stationary sawing machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies machinery which primarily perform material sawing operations.
metadata.includes: Arm saws, radial saws; band saws; table saws
metadata.excludes: Construction, logging, and mining machinery (32); food slicers, meat grinders (361); paper production machinery (364); textile, apparel, leather production machinery (366); sawing handtools (712)

metadata.title: Stationary sawing machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily performs material sawing operations where a more specific code from 3551 to 3559 cannot be determined.
metadata.includes: Cutoff saws

metadata.title: Stationary saws— arm
metadata.definition: A radial arm saw is a cutting machine consisting of a circular saw mounted on a sliding horizontal arm.
metadata.includes: Radial arm saws

metadata.title: Stationary saws— band
metadata.definition: A power saw with a long, sharp blade consisting of a continuous band of toothed metal stretched between two or more wheels to cut material.

metadata.title: Stationary saws— table
metadata.definition: A table with a circular saw blade protruding through the top.
metadata.includes: Saw bench

metadata.title: Stationary sawing machinery—stationary— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Machinery which primarily perform material sawing operations that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3551 through 3553.
metadata.includes: Abrasive saws, diamond saws, agitating saws

metadata.title: Other metal, wood, and special material machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies metal, woodworking, and special material machinery which perform specific functions other than those previously classified in 351 through 355.
metadata.includes: Recycling densifier, Ultrasonic machinery (USM) electrochemical and discharge machinery (EDM's); laser cutting machinery; pressure fluid cutting machinery; spot and other welding machinery
metadata.excludes: Agricultural and garden machinery (31); material and personnel handling machinery (34); food slicers, meat grinders (361); paper production machinery (364); textile, apparel, leather production machinery (366); painting, priming, metal coating machinery (3546); Handtools, handheld power saws, powered surfacing handtools, welding and heating handtools (71)

metadata.title: Other metal, wood, and special material machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Metal, woodworking, and special material machinery where a more specific code from 3591 to 3599 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Electrochemical and discharge machinery (EDM)
metadata.definition: Machinery that utilize electrical discharges to perform micro machining and precision machining tasks. They are often used for machining glass or ceramic materials.
metadata.includes: Electrochemical machinery (ECM)

metadata.title: Laser cutting machinery
metadata.definition: Machines that employ lasers to make precise cuts. They are often applied to cut structural and piping materials and flat sheet material (i.e. metal).
metadata.includes: Carbon-dioxide lasers, gas lasers

metadata.title: Pressure fluid cutting machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery that employs a high velocity stream of extremely high pressure water to cut materials. The water may or may not contain suspended abrasive particles to aid with cutting.
metadata.includes: Water jet cutting

metadata.title: Engraving machinery
metadata.definition: Machines is used to carve or etch images into materials such as metal, stone, or wood.

metadata.title: Welding machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery used to separate and join metal materials using high heat.
metadata.includes: Non-autonomous robotic welding machinery
metadata.excludes: Welding, cutting, and blow torches (718); welding fumes (Division 9)

metadata.title: Other metal, wood, and special material machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Special process metal and woodworking machinery that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3591 through 3595.

metadata.title: Special process machinery
metadata.definition: This major group classifies machinery and equipment designed to perform specialized tasks relating to food and beverage processing; medical processes; packaging and wrapping; and paper and textile production.
metadata.includes: Food and beverage processing machinery; medical, surgical, and x-ray machinery and equipment; packaging, bottling, wrapping machinery; paper production machinery; printing machinery and equipment; textile, apparel, leather production machinery; other special process machinery

metadata.title: Special process machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Machinery and equipment designed to perform specialized tasks relating to food and beverage processing; medical processes; packaging and wrapping; and paper and textile production or other special process where a more specific code from 3610 to 3699 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Food and beverage processing machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies special process machinery which are primarily used in the food and beverage industries.
metadata.includes: Food slicers; juice, oil, fat extractors; meat grinders; food and beverage mixers, blenders, whippers; butchering machinery; dairy and milk processing machinery
metadata.excludes: Packaging, bottling, wrapping machinery (363); pressurized cooking and frying machinery (3322); beverage heating and percolating machines (3321); stoves, ovens (3326)

metadata.title: Food and beverage processing machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Special process machinery which are primarily used in the food and beverage industries where a more specific code from 3611 to 3619 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Food slicers
metadata.definition: Machines or appliances that chop or slice food in large quantities

metadata.title: Juice, oil, and fat extractors
metadata.definition: Machines or appliances that extract juices or oils from food products.

metadata.title: Meat grinders
metadata.definition: Machines or appliances that grind and extrude meat into a fine mince.

metadata.title: Mixers, blenders, whippers—food and beverage
metadata.definition: Industrial machinery and appliances that mix and combine food.

metadata.title: Butchering machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery used to break down and process slaughtered animals for meat product production.
metadata.includes: Skinning machinery, deboning machinery, filleting machinery

metadata.title: Dairy and milk processing machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery used in the processing of dairy products.
metadata.includes: Butter-making machinery, homogenizers, clarifiers, cream separators, pasteurizers, evaporators

metadata.title: Food and beverage processing machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Special process machinery which are primarily used in the food and beverage industries that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3611 through 3616.
metadata.includes: Retort machine

metadata.title: Medical and surgical machinery, equipment
metadata.definition: This source group classifies special process machinery which are primarily used in medical applications. X-ray machinery classified here may be used in industrial and other research applications as well as medical usage.
metadata.includes: Medical machinery and equipment; x-ray, magnetic resonance imaging (MRIs), fluoroscope machinery and equipment
metadata.excludes: Medical and surgical instruments, health care and orthopedic equipment, n.e.c. (749)

metadata.title: Medical and surgical machinery, equipment— unspecified
metadata.definition: Special process machinery which are primarily used in medical applications where a more specific code from 3621 to 3629 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Medical imaging and radiological machinery, equipment
metadata.definition: Medical imaging equipment that involves use of radioactive materials. This code also includes machinery that uses x-ray technology for non-medical purposes.
metadata.includes: X-ray, magnetic resonance imaging (MRI), and fluoroscope, fluoroscopic x-ray, therapeutic x-ray, radiographic x-ray, computed tomography (CT); HIDA scan; security scan x-ray machines; ultrasound equipment

metadata.title: Surgical and medical robots
metadata.definition: Machinery that move in an unsupervised or supervised manor while performing surgical and medical tasks.
metadata.includes: Surgical robots; human-operated surgical robots

metadata.title: Medical and surgical machinery, equipment— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Special process machinery which are primarily used in medical applications that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3621 through 3622.
metadata.includes: Monitors; ventilators; medication pumps; defibrillators
metadata.excludes: Mechanical hospital beds, mechanical mobility devices (e.g. scooters, powered wheelchairs) (743)

metadata.title: Packaging, bottling, wrapping machinery
metadata.definition: This source group classifies special process machinery which primarily perform packaging, bottling, and wrapping operations.
metadata.includes: Bottling, canning, filling machinery; packaging, wrapping, bundling machinery (including boxing machinery); product labeling machinery; sealing, stapling machinery

metadata.title: Packaging, bottling, wrapping machinery— unspecified
metadata.definition: Packaging, bottling, and wrapping machinery where a more specific code from 3631 to 3639 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Bottling, canning, filling machinery
metadata.definition: Machines that fill bottles and cans with product and seals them closed.

metadata.title: Packaging, wrapping, bundling machinery

metadata.includes: Sealing, stapling machinery

metadata.title: Product labeling machinery
metadata.definition: Machines that label by stamping or affixing labels to product.

metadata.title: Banding, baling, strapping machinery

metadata.title: Packaging, bottling, wrapping machinery— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Packaging, bottling, and wrapping machinery that are specified but do not meet descriptions of codes 3631 through 3634.

metadata.title: Rollers, calenders, dryers—paper production

metadata.title: Printing machinery— n.e.c.

metadata.title: Textile, apparel, leather production machinery

metadata.definition: Special process machinery and equipment which are primarily employed in the textile, apparel, and leather production where a more specific code from 3661 to 3669 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Picking, carding, combing machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery that processes raw fibers by removing dirt and debris and straitening fibers into bundles or rovings for spinning.

metadata.title: Spinning machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery that spins loose fibers into thread or yarn.

metadata.title: Textile dyeing machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery that applies colored dyes to yarn, threads and textiles.

metadata.title: Knitting, weaving machinery
metadata.definition: Machinery that creates fabric from yarn or thread by means of weaving or knitting.

metadata.title: Sewing, stitching machinery
